// Circular dependency detection
// A depends on B, B depends on A:
// 1. Creating A -> needs B -> creating B -> needs A
// 2. A is in 'currently creating' set
// 3. Spring detects cycle for constructor injection -> throws
// 4. For field injection: Spring uses 'early bean reference'
//    (the proxy before full initialization) to break the cycle
//    This is why @Autowired field injection CAN have circular deps
//    but constructor injection CANNOT

// What Spring does internally for @Autowired

// AutowiredAnnotationBeanPostProcessor.postProcessProperties():
// 1. metadata = findAutowiringMetadata(bean.getClass())
//    -> scans for @Autowired, caches result
// 2. metadata.inject(bean, beanName, pvs)
//    -> for each InjectedElement:
//       element.inject(target, beanName, pvs)

// For field injection (AutowiredFieldElement.inject()):
// Object value = beanFactory.resolveDependency(
//     new DependencyDescriptor(field, required), beanName);
// field.setAccessible(true);
// field.set(bean, value);

